-- Algeria Plans to Raise Refining Capacity 18%, El Moudjahid Says
-- B y   S a l a h   S l i m a n i
-- 2012-05-28T11:26:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-28/algeria-plans-to-raise-refining-capacity-18-el-moudjahid-says.html
Algeria ’s Sonatrach plans to increase
its oil refining capacity by 18 percent, the company’s chief
executive officer told the government daily El Moudjahid.  Capacity will rise by 4 million metric tons to 26 million
tons a year or 440,000 barrels a day, CEO Abdelhamid Zerguine
was cited as saying in the newspaper.  Work on the Skikda refinery is to be completed in August
and the Algiers plant will be finished next year, according to
the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salah Slimani in Cairo at 
